25 16-120-805. Firearms hold agreement — Limitation.
26 (a) As used in this section:
27 (1) "Federal firearms licensee" means a person licensed under 18
28 U.S.C. §§ 921-934, as they existed on January 1, 2024;
29 (2) "Firearm" means the same as defined in § 5-1-102; and
30 (3) "Firearm hold agreement" means a transaction between a
31 federal firearms licensee and an individual firearm owner in which the
32 federal firearms licensee takes physical possession of the individual firearm
33 owner’s lawfully possessed firearm at the owner's request, holds the firearm
34 for an agreed period of time, and returns the firearm to the individual
35 firearm owner according to the terms of the transaction.
36 (b)(1) A federal firearms licensee operating lawfully in the
